HEADWORD: Proveditor
<hw>Pro*ved"i*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>proveditore</ets>, <ets>provveditore</ets>, fr.
<ets>provedere</ets>, L. <ets>providere</ets>. See <er>Provide</er>, and
cf. <er>Purveyor</er>, <er>Provedore</er>.]</ety> <def>One employed to
procure supplies, as for an army, a steamer, etc.; a purveyor; one who
provides for another.</def> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provedore</ent>⟦br⟧
